The paper deals with the problem of sorting integers, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AL). The use of radix sorting and the analysis of time and space complexity suggest that the paper may also belong to the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the mention of O(1) extra space and the extension to read-only keys suggest that the paper may also belong to the category of information theory (cs.IT).
